        googletag.cmd.push(function () {
          googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1404853927369-9');
        });
      }
    </script>
  </div>
</div>

  </div>

          <div>  <div class="section section--separator">
          <div id="how-to-set-and-accomplish-goals" class="section-anchor skip-inline-link-filter"></div>
                      <div class="h2 section-title">
            How to Set and Accomplish Goals
      </div>
        <div class="section__body">
                      
            <article>
  
      
              <img src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_180x180/public/2021-01/shutterstock_334592678.jpg?itok=yXrJgMQe" width="180" height="180" alt="" title="Ivan Kruk/Shutterstock" loading="lazy" />



      
  </article>

      
                    
            <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Achieving a goal is a process. And all of the components of that process deserve <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/attention" title="Psychology Today looks at attention" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">attention</a> to ensure success, from setting the objective, to overcoming obstacles, to sustaining momentum until the project is complete.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
      
        </div>
          
          
<div class="faqs">
                                                            <div class="faq faq--1">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How should I set my goals?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Failing to accomplish a goal is sometimes due to the way it was set. But a few <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/the-savvy-psychologist/202001/4-psychological-tricks-reach-your-goals">psychological tricks can help set and reach those goals.</a> One is to ensure that the goal is attached to a value, such as the value of supporting your local community or fighting <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/environment" title="Psychology Today looks at climate change" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">climate change</a>. Another is to frame your goal as an asset to be gained rather than a threat to be avoided. For example, instead of thinking, &ldquo;I shouldn&rsquo;t bother my boss, so we can avoid a rocky relationship,&rdquo; try thinking, &ldquo;I want to learn new communication skills to reset our relationship.&rdquo; Yet another idea is to try setting a learning goal instead of a performance goal; instead of deciding to lose 20 pounds, decide to learn more about <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/diet" title="Psychology Today looks at nutrition" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">nutrition</a> and cook two healthy recipes each week.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--2">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How do I build momentum?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Motivation targets the &ldquo;why&rdquo; of change, but momentum targets the &ldquo;how.&rdquo; <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/fostering-freedom/201910/how-generate-momentum">Generating momentum is pivotal</a> for taking the concrete steps needed to shift out of entrenched patterns and make change. Focusing on momentum can also be used in a therapeutic context. For example, a therapist might address a pattern of avoidance in a patient with <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/depression" title="Psychology Today looks at depression" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">depression</a> by identifying small steps they have already taken (getting out of bed that morning, coming to <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/therapy" title="Psychology Today looks at therapy" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">therapy</a>) and then listing the next steps they can take next. Recognizing the motivation for change and focusing on the dynamics that support change can also help build momentum.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--3 collapsed">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How do I persevere through difficult tasks?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>It&rsquo;s natural to feel stuck at certain points, especially when <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/between-cultures/202003/4-strategies-persevering-through-difficult-tasks">working through difficult tasks.</a> But research suggests that several strategies can help. One is to focus on the positive consequences of the activity, such as passing a final exam. Another is to try and regulate your emotions during the task, such as by thinking about an upcoming vacation while running on the treadmill. Yet another is to monitor and track your progress, which can continue to propel you toward the next milestone. Lastly, try to enrich the task and make it more enjoyable (called &ldquo;temptation bundling&rdquo;), like listening to a podcast as you do the laundry.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--4 collapsed faq--last">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How do I accomplish my goals?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Tracking progress is key to sustaining motivation and <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/brainstorm/202002/perceptual-tricks-help-you-achieve-your-goals">achieving your goals.</a> It&rsquo;s helpful to make progress visual and concrete, such as by writing it down or using an app. Tracking can also help you spot patterns that might derail your success. For example, health and wellness goals are generally long-term. Tracking your progress and behavior can help you spot when you tend to slip up, and then address the underlying causes. Additionally, it can be motivating to reflect back on the progress you&rsquo;ve made, or look forward to the work to come if it&rsquo;s a core part of your identity.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                        </div>

    
        
  </div>
</div>
          <div>  <div class="section section--separator">
          <div id="how-to-increase-motivation" class="section-anchor skip-inline-link-filter"></div>
                      <div class="h2 section-title">
            How to Increase Motivation
      </div>
        <div class="section__body">
                      
            <article>
  
      
              <img src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_180x180/public/2021-01/shutterstock_1237790389.jpg?itok=-mwuJvM_" width="180" height="180" alt="" title="Shcherbyna Nataliia/Shutterstock" loading="lazy" />



      
  </article>

      
                    
            <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Some people may find themselves completely stymied by a project; others may simply want to pack a little more <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/productivity" title="Psychology Today looks at productivity" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">productivity</a> into their timeline. No matter where motivation begins, there are always ways to increase it&mdash;whether that be your own motivation or someone else&rsquo;s.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
      
        </div>
          
          
<div class="faqs">
                                                            <div class="faq faq--1">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can I feel more motivated?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Sometimes you <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/get-out-your-mind/201903/don-t-feel-motivated-play-the-impossible-game">might feel completely unmotivated</a>&mdash;and that&rsquo;s ok. In that situation, allow yourself to feel the discomfort, hear the negative <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/self-talk" title="Psychology Today looks at self-talk" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">self-talk</a>, and then take action anyway, For example, let&rsquo;s say you come home after a long day at work and just want to unwind and watch TV. Instead of turning the TV on, acknowledge that you&rsquo;re tired and then challenge yourself to read five pages of the book on your nightstand first. This approach gives space for negative thoughts and feelings, while helping you change ingrained patterns.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--2">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can I stop procrastinating?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p><a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/procrastination" title="Psychology Today looks at Procrastination" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">Procrastination</a> is often driven by underlying feelings of distress or <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/anxiety" title="Psychology Today looks at anxiety" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">anxiety</a> elicited by a given task. But there are ways to <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/fulfillment-any-age/201611/12-ways-beat-procrastination">navigate the discomfort and beat procrastination.</a> You can break the project into small, more manageable pieces; accomplishing one step will fuel your motivation for the next. You can set limits for the time spent preparing to begin, or aim to complete tasks as quickly as possible. You can also set a reward that you&rsquo;ll get after completing the task or a part of it.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--3 collapsed">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can companies motivate their employees?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Companies have the opportunity to motivate employees with incentives, but they also need to be <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/mindfulness" title="Psychology Today looks at mindful" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">mindful</a> that incentives can backfire&mdash;as in the case of the Wells Fargo scandal. <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/creative-leadership/202004/extrinsic-vs-intrinsic-motivation-work">Employees are motivated</a> by external rewards when they believe that working harder will lead to a better performance, that they&rsquo;ll be rewarded for a better performance, and they appreciate the reward, such as a bonus or time off. It can be difficult to meet those criteria&mdash;&ldquo;Will my hard work really be noticed?&rdquo; &ldquo;Does my contribution really matter since I&rsquo;m on a large team?&mdash;so companies should tailor incentives to each unique team and role.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--4 collapsed faq--last">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can politicians motivate their constituents?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p><a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/articles/201701/the-mystery-motivation">Successful interventions often motivate</a> through a combination of psychology and economic policy, which vary by context but often leverage social norms. For example, more people enrolled in a sustainable energy program when the sign up sheet was in their building lobby, because they could showcase their values to their neighbors&mdash;or perhaps feel pressured to sign up to maintain a good reputation.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                        </div>

    
        
  </div>
</div>
          <div>  <div class="section section--separator">
          <div id="diet-exercise-and-finance-goals" class="section-anchor skip-inline-link-filter"></div>
                      <div class="h2 section-title">
            Diet, Exercise, and Finance Goals
      </div>
        <div class="section__body">
                      
            <article>
  
      
              <img src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_180x180/public/2021-01/shutterstock_151886987.jpg?itok=VF33UFcM" width="180" height="180" alt="" title="Lolostock/Shutterstock" loading="lazy" />



      
  </article>

      
                    
            <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Some of the most common goals people make&mdash;and the most common goals they struggle to meet&mdash;are to eat healthier, work out more, and save more money. Many traps can prevent people from achieving those goals, but anticipating those challenges can help achieve real change.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
      
        </div>
          
          
<div class="faqs">
                                                            <div class="faq faq--1">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can I stick to my diet?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Many people struggle to stick to a diet. Research suggests that extrinsic motivators&mdash;to avoid hurtful comments or fit into an outfit&mdash;can jumpstart the process but that intrinsic motivation&mdash;interest, enjoyment, and challenge in the journey&mdash;is key to <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/never-binge-again/201912/permanent-weight-loss-motivation-what-it-takes">sustained, lasting weight loss.</a> Intrinsic motivation encompasses competence, autonomy, and relatedness, so it&rsquo;s helpful to 1) choose a diet that will be sustainable and effective 2) believe that the diet, start date, and end goals have been chosen autonomously and not &ldquo;assigned&rdquo; by others 3) find a community of supporters.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--2">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can I stay motivated to exercise?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>There are a few creative ideas to consider <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/practical-approach-addressing-barriers-physical-activity/202010/3-techniques-use-if-motivation">if motivation is a barrier to exercise.</a> One is to widen the options you have: If you don&rsquo;t have time to go to the gym, exercise by going for a walk, doing a bodyweight circuit, or watching a yoga video. Another is to make exercise more enjoyable, such as by listening to a book on tape. Yet another is to establish a social contract with a friend or family member. For example, if you allow phone time to supersede exercise, you must donate to a cause of the other person&rsquo;s choosing.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--3 collapsed">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How do I motivate myself to save money?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Four steps can help <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/the-science-behind-behavior/201803/4-steps-cultivate-the-habit-saving-money">cultivate the habit of saving money.</a> The first is to set a specific saving goal for an emergency fund. This focused goal will build habits that become sustainable saving. The second is to save something every day, even if it&rsquo;s just a few dollars, because repetition helps to form habits. Third, making savings visible, whether by checking a savings account online or keeping cash in a glass jar. Fourth, consistently spend less than you make&mdash;in addition to cultivating a saving mindset, it&rsquo;s important to change a spending mindset.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--4 collapsed faq--last">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How can I follow through on my New Year&#039;s resolutions?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Most people, unfortunately, <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/supersurvivors/202101/so-you-set-new-year-s-resolution-now-what">fail to follow through on their New Year&rsquo;s resolutions.</a> This might be because people tend to set overwhelming goals, engage in all-or-nothing thinking, don&rsquo;t anticipate obstacles, and beat themselves up when they get off track. By addressing those traps&mdash;such as by breaking large goals into smaller pieces or thinking of results as a range of positive outcomes rather than &ldquo;success or failure&rdquo;&mdash;people are more likely to truly achieve their goals.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                        </div>

    
        
  </div>
</div>
      </div>


      </div>
    
    
    
                
